def: Of or pertaining to the tarsus (either of the foot or eye).-- n.
Applied to the Romance languages, as being mostly of Latinorigin.

An order of pelagic Hydrozoa including species which formcomplex free-swimming communities composed of numerous zooids ofvarious kinds, some of which act as floats or as swimming organs,others as feeding or nutritive zooids, and others as reproductivezooids. See Illust. under Physallia, and Porpita.

Furnished with quills; also, shaped like quills. "A sharp-quilled porcupine." Shak. Quilled suture (Surg.), a variety of stitchin which the threads after being passed deeply through the edges of awound are secured about two quills or bodies of similar shape, inorder to produce a suitable degree of pressure.
Forming again; having the quality of renewing form;reformatory. Good.
Feeding upon ants; -- said of certain birds.

The earth alumina, as found native in a crystalline state,including sapphire, which is the fine blue variety; the orientalruby, or red sapphire; the oriental amethyst, or purple sapphire; andadamantine spar, the hair-brown variety. It is the hardest substancefound native, next to the diamond.
Smeared with bitumen. [R.] "The hatches caulked and bitumed."Shak.
The state or quality of being immane; barbarity. [R.] Shak.
